  On Your Photos Question
                                                                                                                                                                                                                
  Short answer: not on GitHub. Here's why:
                                                                                                                                                                                                                
  - GitHub is for code — it handles large image files poorly and has size limits                                                                                                                                
  - Cloudinary is where your actual artwork photos live — it's built for this, serves images fast globally, and has a free tier that'll cover you well                                                          
  - You just upload photos to Cloudinary, and your code references them by URL                                                                                                                                  
                                                                                                                                                                                                                
  So the structure is:                                                                                                                                                                                          
  GitHub     → your code                                                                                                                                                                                        
  Cloudinary → your artwork photos                                                                                                                                                                              
  Vercel     → runs it all live   

